# React to Vue 3 Conversion Plan: da-cheng-lok-lok

This plan outlines the steps to convert the existing React-based `da-cheng-lok-lok` project into a fresh Vue 3 application.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> I will be creating a new directory `da-cheng-lok-lok-vue` for this project to keep it separate from the React source and the previous `v3` attempt.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Setup
- [NEW] Initialize Vue 3 + Vite project in `da-cheng-lok-lok-vue`.
- [NEW] Install dependencies (`vue-router`, `lucide-vue-next`, `motion` etc. matching React dependencies).

### Component Migration
- [NEW] Convert `src/components/*` React components to [.vue](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/antigravity/da-cheng-lok-lok-v3/src/App.vue) files.
- [NEW] Convert `src/screens/*` to Vue views/components.
- [NEW] Migrate [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/antigravity/da-cheng-lok-lok/src/App.tsx) logic to [App.vue](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/antigravity/da-cheng-lok-lok-v3/src/App.vue).
- [NEW] Copy and adapt [constants.ts](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/antigravity/da-cheng-lok-lok/src/constants.ts) and [types.ts](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/antigravity/da-cheng-lok-lok/src/types.ts).
- [NEW] Apply [index.css](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/antigravity/da-cheng-lok-lok/src/index.css) styles.

### Logic & Features
- Implement state management (Ref/Reactive) matching the React state.
- Set up Routing if applicable.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `npm run build` to ensure no compilation errors.

### Manual Verification
- `npm run dev` to preview the application and verify layout/interaction.
